President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate James H. Anderson for the position of Assistant Secretary of Defense for Strategy, Plans, and Capabilities. Anderson is currently the Vice President of Academic Affairs at Marine Corps University and has previously served as the Director of Middle East Policy in the Office of the Secretary of Defense. He has also served as an intelligence officer in the United States Marine Corps. President Trump has also announced his intent to appoint Christopher D. Miller as Chairman of the United States Section of the Permanent Joint Board on Defense for the United States and Canada, and Meaghan C. Mobbs and R. James Nicholson as Members of the Board of Visitors to the United States Military Academy.